translation[11]{c,v,t}:
  11,98,Qayamat ke roz woh apni qaum ke aagey aagey hoga aur apni peshwayi mein unhein dozakh ki taraf le jayega. Kaisi badhtar jaye wurood (wretched destination) hai yeh jis par koi pahunche
  11,99,Aur un logon par duniya mein bhi laanat padi aur qayamat ke roz bhi padeygi. Kaisa bura sila hai yeh jo kisi ko miley
  11,100,Yeh chand bastiyaon ki sarguzisht (account) hai jo hum tumhein suna rahey hain. Inmein se baaz ab bhi khadi hain aur baaz ki fasal kat chuki hai
  11,101,"Humne unpar zulm nahin kiya, unhon ne aap hi apne upar sitam dhaya. Aur jab Allah ka hukum aa gaya to unke woh mabood jinhein woh Allah ko chodh kar pukara karte thay unke kuch kaam na aa sakey. Aur unhon ne halakat o barbadi ke siwa unhein kuch faiyda na diya"
  11,102,"Aur tera Rubb jab kisi zalim basti ko pakadta hai to phir uski pakad aisi hi hua karti hai, fil waqeh uski pakad badi sakht aur dardnaak hoti hai"
  11,103,Haqeeqat yeh hai ke is mein ek nishani hai har us shaks ke liye jo azaab e aakhirat ka khauf karey. Woh ek din hoga jismein sab log jamaa hongey aur phir jo kuch bhi us roz hoga sab ki aankhon ke saamne hoga
  11,104,"Hum uske laney mein kuch bahut zyada takheer nahin kar rahey hain, bas ek gini chuni muddat uske liye muqarrar hai"
  11,105,"Jab woh aayega to kisi ko baat karne ki majal na hogi, illa yeh ke khuda ki ijazat se kuch arz karey, phir kuch log us roz badbakht hongey aur kuch neik bakht"
  11,106,Jo bad-bakht hongey woh dozakh mein jayenge (jahan garmi aur pyas ki shiddat se). Woh hanpenge aur phunkare marenge (sigh and groan)
  11,107,"Aur usi halat mein woh hamesha rahenge jab tak ke zameen o aasman qayam hain, illa yeh ke tera Rubb kuch aur chahe. Beshak tera Rubb poora ikhtiyar rakhta hai ke jo chahe karey"
  11,108,"Rahey woh log jo neik bakht niklenge , to woh jannat mein jayenge aur wahan hamesha rahenge jab tak zameen o aasman qayam hain, illa yeh ke tera Rubb kuch aur chache. Aisi bakshish unko milegi jiska silsila kabhi munqata (khatam) na hoga"